data.title: Fischer games 1956 1963

data.text: 1. The document describes several chess games played by Robert Fischer at the 1955 US Junior Championship in Lincoln, Nebraska and the 1956 Canadian Open in Montreal. 2. In one game at the US Junior Championship, the 13-year old Fischer defeated Viktors Pupols using the black pieces in 41 moves. 3. At the 1956 Canadian Open, Fischer drew against Heinz Matthai in a 103-move game that saw both players' queens captured and promoted pawns on the board.
